HB92 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3 To propose an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
4 of 2022, relating to Tuscaloosa County, to authorize the
5 mayors of municipalities in the county to participate in the
6 Employees' Retirement System of Alabama under the same terms
7 and conditions as other employees in the same retirement
8 system.
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
10 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
11 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
12 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
13 In Tuscaloosa County, full-time mayors of
14 municipalities in the county may participate in the Employees'
15 Retirement System of Alabama under the same terms and
16 conditions as other employees in the same retirement system.
17 Any mayor holding office at the time of the ratification of
18 this amendment shall be eligible to purchase service credit in
19 the Employees' Retirement System for the time the official has
20 served in the current office. No individual may participate in
21 both a supernumerary program and the Employees' Retirement
22 System based on the same service.
23 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
24 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
25 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
26 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
27 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
28 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
Page 1

for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
HB92 Enrolled
29 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
30 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
31 language; and translate effective dates.
32 END PROPOSED AMENDMENT
33 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
34 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284, 284.01, and 285
35 of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws
36 of this state. The appropriate election official shall assign
37 a ballot number for the proposed constitutional amendment on
38 the election ballot and shall set forth the following
39 description of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
40 constitutional amendment:
41 "Relating to Tuscaloosa County, proposing an amendment
42 to the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to authorize the
43 full-time mayors of municipalities in the county to
44 participate in the Employees' Retirement System of Alabama
45 under the same terms and conditions as other employees in the
46 same retirement system.
47 Proposed by Act ____."
48 This description shall be followed by the following
49 language:
50 "Yes( ) No( )."
51 Section 3. The proposed amendment shall become valid as
52 part of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, when approved by
53 a majority of the qualified electors voting thereon.
